The problem is this
$$\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
    \nabla . (C(x)  : \nabla_s u(x))  + \omega^2\rho(x)u(x)  &= 0\\\
    u(x +  h_i)  &= u(x)\text{exp}(ik.h_i)\\\
    \sigma(x + h_i). n(x + h_i) &= \sigma(x).n(x)\text{exp}(ik.h_i)
\end{aligned}
\end{equation}$$
I am solving a simplified 1-D problem where the $C(x)$ term becomes $E$. I am using MatDiffusion kernel for this and for the other term MassEigenKernel. The two equations below are the boundary conditions.

